<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98648807893220></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98648807893220><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=2&mid=98648807893220>RE: roge</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=2&mid=98648807893220#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Apr 5th 12:27 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I haved played both a wood elf and dwarf rogue. Wood elves are nice because of the agi/dex staring points, but there str is a little low. The dwarf now, has better starting str and decent agi/dex stats. I found have it easier to get items that agi and dex, instead of str, but that is just me. I think the dwarves make a better rogue type char. Short and stealthy. This is just my 2cp.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
